<title>USA: Continental seeks pilot contract by July 1.</title>
<headline>Continental seeks pilot contract by July 1.</headline>
<dateline>HOUSTON 1997-04-01</dateline>
<text>
<p>Continental Airlines Inc said on Tuesday evening that it aimed to have a new labor contract with its pilots by July 1.</p>
<p>The carrier, its sister company Continental Express and the union representing about 5,000 of their pilots plan to open talks on Wednesday.</p>
<p>&quot;Our pilots deserve more pay, and we plan to pay them more -- just like we've done with all other employees during the past year,&quot; Continental said in a release.</p>
<p>&quot;We're going to commit the necessary resources so we can have a contract by July 1, the amendable date. There is no reason not to have a contract by that date,&quot; it said.</p>
</text>
